The article discusses President Obama's call for businesses to offer more educational benefits and paid apprenticeships to help workers earn higher-paying jobs. The article highlights the success of the registered apprenticeship program and the President's commitment to expanding it further. It also mentions several major employers that are committing to expanding apprenticeship programs and providing educational opportunities for their employees. The article discusses the efforts of the White House to convene employers, educators, labor, and philanthropy to take additional steps to support the job progression of hardworking Americans. It also outlines executive actions and legislative proposals to expand apprenticeship and training, as well as new investments in high-quality training for workers. The article concludes by calling on Congress to pass bipartisan legislation to help more workers get ahead and more businesses invest in the skills they need.